==English==
===Transitive verb===
'''to [[know]] (something) [[like]] the [[back]] of [[one's]] [[hand]]'''

#To be intimately familiar with something.  To know every smallest detail about something.  Frequently used in reference to a particular locale.  Usually not used when referring to another person.

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[kennen als z'n broekzak]]
*Finnish: [[tuntea kuin omat taskunsa]] (know like own pockets)
*French: [[connaître comme sa poche]] (know like one's pocket)
*Swedish: [[känna som sin egen ficka]] (know like one's pocket)
